data.description: Close to downtown, corner lot in historical Olmos Park Terrace,  this residence stands as a testament to architectural elegance and timeless beauty. Originally constructed by the renowned Herman C. Thorman, this home has been thoughtfully restored to blend its historic charm with modern comforts, resulting in an exceptional living experience that captures the essence of refined living. A new master suite has been expertly integrated, offering a private haven of relaxation. The heart of the home unveils an open-concept design that seamlessly blends the kitchen, formal dining, and living areas. High-end appliances, ample counter space, and custom cabinetry combine to create a culinary haven for the most discerning of chefs. The living room boasts a fireplace that stands as a focal point of elegance and warmth. The exterior boasts a large & manicured backyard. Enjoy lower city taxes due to the historical tax rate. Work/ Live space. Zoned R-4: residential & and O-1 (Small and medium office uses, attorney, banks, worship facilities, public and private school, employment agency, library, medical clinic, optician, interior decorator studio). Schedule your private tour today.
